    Display the HR forest plot, along with its KM plots

    hr_forestly.Rd

    Display the HR forest plot, along with its KM plots

    hr_forestly(
  outdata,
  time_unit = c("days", "weeks", "months", "years"),
  y_label_kmplot = "Survival Probability",
  width = 1000,
  height_kmoplot = 400,
  height_at_risk = 200,
  max_page = NULL
)

    Arguments

    outdata

    outdata An outdata object created by format_hr_forestly().

    time_unit

    A string specifying the unit of time in x-axis of the KM plot. must be one of "days", "weeks", "months", or "years". Default is "days".

    y_label_kmplot

    A string specifying the y-axis label of the KM plot. Default is "Survival Probability".

    width

    A numeric value of width of the entire plot in pixels. Default is 1000.

    height_kmoplot

    A numeric value of height of the KM plot in pixels. Default is 400.

    height_at_risk

    A numeric value of height of the at-risk table in pixels. Default is 200.

    max_page

    A numeric value of maximum number of subgroups to display per page.

    Value

    An HR forest plot with subgroup KM plot saved as a shiny.tag.list object.

    Examples

    prepare_hr_forestly(
  meta = meta_tte_example_new(),
  population = "apat",
  observation = "efficacy_population",
  endpoint = "pfs;os",
  subgroup = "male;female",
  arm_levels = c("Placebo", "Xanomeline Low Dose", "Xanomeline High Dose")
) |>
  format_hr_forestly() |>
  hr_forestly()
